            "text": "Mesenchymal stem cells ( MSCs ) have been extensively investigated for the treatment of various diseases . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "The therapeutic potential of MSCs is attributed to complex cellular and molecular mechanisms of action",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "including differentiation into multiple cell lineages and regulation of immune responses via immunomodulation . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 2,
            "text": "The plasticity of MSCs in immunomodulation allow these cells to exert different immune effects",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "depending on different diseases . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Understanding the biology of MSCs and their role in treatment is critical",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 6,
            "text": "to determine their potential for various therapeutic applications and for the development of MSC - based regenerative medicine . <S>",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "This review summarizes the recent progress of particular mechanisms",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "underlying the tissue regenerative properties and immunomodulatory effects of MSCs . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 8,
            "text": "We focused on discussing the functional roles of paracrine activities , direct cell - cell contact , mitochondrial transfer , and extracellular vesicles",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 10,
            "text": "related to MSC - mediated effects on immune cell responses , cell survival , and regeneration . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
